---
/**
 * Routing logic — design doc §8 anti-pattern #3 + §9 bold choice.
 * Three-claim cards above, routing-logic code-comment block below.
 */
import Container from "./Container.astro";
import Section from "./Section.astro";
import TextBlock from "./TextBlock.astro";
---

<Section>
  <Container>
    <TextBlock align="center">
      <h2>Route smarter. Pay less. See everything.</h2>
    </TextBlock>

    <div class="cards">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Route by tier, not by guessing.</h3>
        <p>
          Pick a tier &mdash; cheap, balanced, or premium. InferBridge
          handles the rest: which provider, which model, what to do when
          one fails. Override per-request when you need surgical control.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>See every token, every rupee.</h3>
        <p>
          Per-request logs with tokens, latency, cost, and provider. One
          endpoint answers &ldquo;where is my money going?&rdquo; for the
          first time. Aggregate it by mode, provider, or time range.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Indian providers, first-class.</h3>
        <p>
          Sarvam and self-hosted endpoints ship on day one. Add
          <code>X-InferBridge-Residency: india</code> to route only to
          India-hosted infrastructure. No other gateway does this.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <pre class="routing"><code><span class="c"># Your app</span>
client.chat.completions.create(<span class="s">model=<span class="acc">"ib/balanced"</span></span>, ...)

         ↓  InferBridge evaluates:

         <span class="k">model: </span><span class="acc">"ib/cheap"</span>       → Together (Llama 3.3 70B)
         <span class="k">model: </span><span class="acc">"ib/balanced"</span>    → OpenAI (gpt-4o-mini)
         <span class="k">model: </span><span class="acc">"ib/premium"</span>     → Anthropic (claude-opus-4-7)
         <span class="k">residency: </span><span class="acc">"india"</span>      → Sarvam (sarvam-m)
         <span class="k">fallback: </span><span class="acc">on 5xx/429</span>    → next candidate in tier

         ↓  Your app receives: standard OpenAI response</code></pre>

    <TextBlock align="center">
      <p class="caption">
        Real routing logic, not marketing. Override any decision per-request.
        <br />
        Gateway adds ~150ms of overhead. Your model is still the rate-limit.
      </p>
    </TextBlock>
  </Container>
</Section>

<style>
  h2 {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
    margin-block: 56px 56px;
  }

  .card {
    background-color: var(--gray-900);
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-700);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 28px 24px;
  }

  .card h3 {
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: var(--gray-50);
  }

  .card p {
    color: var(--gray-300);
    font-size: var(--fs-body-sm);
    line-height: var(--lh-body-sm);
  }

  .card code {
    font-size: 0.8em;
    background-color: var(--gray-800);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: var(--accent-text);
  }

  .routing {
    background-color: var(--gray-800);
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-700);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-muted);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 32px 32px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-code-block);
    line-height: var(--lh-code-block);
    color: var(--gray-100);
    overflow-x: auto;
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  }

  .routing code {
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: inherit;
    white-space: pre;
  }

  .c {
    color: var(--gray-300);
  }

  .k {
    color: var(--gray-300);
  }

  .acc {
    color: var(--accent-text);
  }

  .caption {
    color: var(--gray-300);
    font-size: var(--fs-caption);
    text-align: center;
    margin-block-start: 20px;
    letter-spacing: var(--ls-caption);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cards {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 16px;
      margin-block: 40px 40px;
    }
    .routing {
      padding: 20px 16px;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
    }
  }
</style>
